city.cs.engine

Class Fixture

  • java.lang.Object
    • city.cs.engine.Fixture
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GhostlyFixture, Sensor, SolidFixture

    public abstract class Fixture
extends Object
    A component of a rigid body. A body can have multiple fixtures but each fixture remains part of a single body. A fixture can be destroyed, removing it from the body, but cannot be attached to another body.

    • Method Detail

      • destroy

        public void destroy()
        Remove this fixture from the parent body and the world. This fixture must not be accessed after being destroyed. All fixtures attached to a body are implicitly destroyed when the body is destroyed, so this method is only needed if part of a body is to be destroyed, leaving the rest intact.
